{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-1512"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Luggage, Handbag & Saddlery/Harness Manufacturing"
 :itonami.blueprint/isic-rev5 "1512"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :luggage/manufacturing
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:fair-labor :local-industry :material-sourcing-transparency]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :luggage-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics true
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:robotics :identity :forms :dmn :bpmn :audit-ledger :cae]
 :itonami.blueprint/optional-technologies [:optimization :telemetry]
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "Luggage-Goods Operations Advisor ⊣ Luggage Governor, langgraph-clj
 StateGraph (langgraph.graph, luggage.operation/build), append-only
 audit ledger (luggage.store/ledger + append-ledger!, mem-store).
 Fixes a severe prior gap: this repo previously had NO
 operation.cljc/StateGraph at all -- luggage.sim hand-called
 governor/evaluate directly, bypassing any graph entirely;
 luggage.phase was a plain data map whose OWN docstring FALSELY claimed
 'Built on langgraph-clj StateGraph shape' over an inert, unconsumed
 :nodes/:edges map; luggage.advisor had plain functions only, no
 Advisor protocol and no MockAdvisor -- this fleet's standard pattern
 used by every sibling cloud-itonami-isic-* actor; and NO
 append-ledger!/audit mechanism existed anywhere in luggage.store, not
 dead code -- the concept was entirely absent from src/, despite this
 same file's own :required-technologies [... :audit-ledger] and the
 README's 'immutable audit ledger' line implying one should exist. This
 blueprint nonetheless claimed :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented,
 which was false given all of the above -- the most severe
 self-declared-maturity-vs-reality gap found in this fleet's audit
 process to date.
 Now: a genuinely compiled StateGraph (intake -> advise -> govern ->
 decide -+-> commit / request-approval -> commit / hold) with
 interrupt-before #{:request-approval} + an in-memory checkpointer for
 real human-in-the-loop resume; a real luggage.advisor/Advisor protocol
 with a MockAdvisor record wrapping the SAME four proposal-builder
 functions (batch-log/maintenance/safety-concern/shipment) UNCHANGED;
 luggage.phase/may-auto-commit? genuinely consulted by the :decide node
 for the actor's 0->3 rollout (phase 1: maintenance auto-commits; phase
 2+: production-batch logging joins; safety-concern and shipment
 coordination never auto-commit at any phase, matching the Governor's
 own independent hard/soft blocks); and a real luggage.store/ledger +
 append-ledger! genuinely wired into the :commit/:hold graph nodes, not
 test-only. luggage.governor's hard/soft checks (spec-basis ·
 effect-not-propose · op-not-allowlisted · plant-not-verified ·
 batch-not-verified · process-control-forbidden · safety-concern
 escalation · confidence/high-stakes gate) and luggage.registry's
 closed allowlist/draft constructors are reused UNCHANGED -- this fix
 only wires the existing plant-operations compliance policy into a real
 compiled graph and a real ledger, it does not redesign it.
 Proven end-to-end by test/luggage/operation_test.clj (ledger stays
 empty until a real commit, phase-gated hold vs. auto-commit for the
 SAME proposal at different phases, HARD holds for unverified-batch/
 safety-concern/unallowlisted-op that never reach human approval even
 at phase-3, escalate-then-approve and escalate-then-reject for
 high-stakes shipment coordination, never-auto-commit for
 safety-concern/shipment at every phase) through the REAL compiled
 graph, plus a clojure -M:run demo runner producing real ledger entries
 for every scenario. All pre-existing governor-contract/facts/registry
 tests are unchanged and still passing. CI
 (.github/workflows/ci.yml) was missing entirely and is added in this
 fix."}
